  "prompt": "What books/materials should I use if I am self studying for AP Psych?",
  "response": "Here are some recommended resources for self-studying AP Psychology:\n\nBooks:\n1. \"Barron's AP Psychology\" - Comprehensive review book\n2. \"The Princeton Review: Cracking the AP Psychology Exam\"\n3. \"5 Steps to a 5: AP Psychology\" - Good for practice and strategy\n\nOnline Resources:\n1. Khan Academy (free video lessons)\n2. Crash Course Psychology YouTube channel\n3. AP Psychology study guides on Albert.io\n4. College Board's official AP Psychology course framework\n\nPractice Materials:\n1. Official College Board practice exams\n2. Kaplan or Princeton Review practice tests\n3. Quizlet for flashcards and key terms\n4. Psychology textbooks with online practice questions\n\nWebsites:\n1. APPsychology.com\n2. Psychsite.com\n3. Study.com AP Psychology section\n\nAdditional Recommended Tools:\n- Flashcard apps (Anki, Quizlet)\n- Podcast: \"Psych Exam Review\"\n- YouTube channels: Mometrix Test Preparation, Adam Adds\n\nPro Tips:\n- Create a structured study schedule\n- Focus on understanding concepts, not just memorizing\n- Take multiple practice exams\n- Review AP Psychology exam format and question types",
